data.description: Will not last ling, This St. Petersburg, Florida home presents an appealing 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom property with numerous desirable features. The freshly painted exterior and newer roof provide a welcoming and well-maintained appearance. The fenced yard and 2-car carport offer both security and convenience. Inside, a spacious kitchen provides ample room for cooking and meal preparation. The split bedroom plan enhances privacy, and there's a dedicated dining area for family gatherings.  Additionally, the whole house has been re-plumbed, ensuring peace of mind and functionality. The absence of carpet throughout the house adds a modern touch, and the new windows installed in 2020 enhance energy efficiency and aesthetics. New storm doors further contribute to the property's appeal, providing added protection and style. Moreover, the property's proximity to restaurants ensures easy dining options nearby, while its location less than 7 miles from the beach caters to beach enthusiasts. Finally, the large yard invites outdoor activities and relaxation, making this property an excellent choice for comfortable Florida living.
